# WHAT “cd” MEANS

`cd` means:

```text
change directory
```

You are telling the terminal:

> “Take me into this folder so I can operate from inside it.”

---

# WHY THIS IS NECESSARY

Without this:
the terminal doesn’t know where your files are.

Think of it like:
walking into the control room before touching the controls.

---

# WHAT HAPPENS AFTER YOU RUN IT

Your terminal is now “standing inside”:

```powershell
PrimePathwyOS
```

Now every command operates from there.

